Class BusObject_mxJPO.Connection

private class BusObject_mxJPO.Connection
extends Object
implements Comparable<BusObject_mxJPO.Connection>

The class is used to store information about one connection including all attributes values and the type, name with revision of the connected business object.

compareTo

public int compareTo(BusObject_mxJPO.Connection _compare)
Compares given connection with this connection. The compare is done in this order:
  • compare connection direction
  • if equal compare relationship name
  • if equal compare business object type
  • if equal compare business object name
  • if equal compare business object revision
  • if equal compare attributes with compareToAttr(org.mxupdate.update.BusObject_mxJPO.Connection)

Specified by:
compareTo in interface Comparable<BusObject_mxJPO.Connection>
Parameters:
_compare - connection instance to compare
Returns:
0 if the connections are equal (should not possible...); a value less than 0 if this connection is lexicographically less than the compared connection; a value greater than 0 if this connection is lexicographically greater than the compared connection
See Also:
compareToAttr(org.mxupdate.update.BusObject_mxJPO.Connection)

compareToAttr

protected int compareToAttr(BusObject_mxJPO.Connection _compare)
Compares all attributes values from this connection with the values from the compared connection. If all values of both connections are equal, the connection id's are compared. The attribute values are compare in the order of the attributes (by attribute names).

Parameters:
_compare - connection to compare
Returns:
0 if all attributes values and both connection id's are equal (should not possible...); a value less than 0 if one attribute value is lexicographically less than the compared attribute value; a value greater than 0 if one attribute value is lexicographically greater than the other attribute value
